      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_unknown_03_page02.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <dateline><!--If there's no date line, omit this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                  <name type="place" ref="Id_where"/>
                  <date when="1816-08-04"/>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>
                            My <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">dear Madam</persName>
                     <lb/>
                     <!-- Use if letter has a saluation ("Dear Sir," for example). If not, delete this line.-->
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>We are most sincerely concerned for<lb/>
                    you and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
               </persName> Miles - There is however a<lb/>
                    great consolation in the <unclear>vaccarity</unclear> of his <choice>
                  <orig>per<lb/>
                        fect</orig>
                  <reg>perfect</reg>
               </choice> recovery though his confinement must<lb/>
                    try your patience &amp; his - Men never bear<lb/>
                    illness or <unclear>;</unclear> confinement to the home, so well<lb/>
                    as women - But I daresay <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>Miles </persName> is as<lb/>
                    patient as a <hi rend="underline">man</hi>
               <hi rend="underline">can</hi> be - Give my kind<lb/>
                    remembrance to him with this <choice>
                  <orig>compli<lb/>
                        ment</orig>
                  <reg>compliment</reg>
               </choice>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p> Whenever you are able to go out or if<lb/>
                    you have a friend in Town whom you<lb/>
                    could trust to chuse it for me I should be<lb/>
                    very much obliged by your getting me<lb/>
                    a shawl about the same size as<lb/>
                    my own - But <del/> it is for an elderly lady<lb/>
                    who I think would prefer crimson or<lb/>
                    dark purple <add>or puce</add> for the color - with a <hi rend="underline">narrow</hi>
               <lb/>
                    border or <hi rend="underline">no</hi> border rather than a broad one<lb/>
                    - I am impatient to get this shawl during<lb/>
                    this severe winter as I want to offer it<lb/>
                    to a very dear old aunt &amp; friend who<lb/>
                    cannot<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_unknown_03_page03.jpg"/>
                    
                    like a young person do without comforts -<lb/>
                    &amp; this I know will be a real comfort<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> If the muslin is not bought I will<lb/>
                    give up having it and would rather the<lb/>
                    £ 1 - 10 <unclear/> now in your hands should go<lb/>
                    toward the price of the shawl that it may<lb/>
                    be a handsome one - I can afford to go as<lb/>
                    far as seven guineas <hi rend="underline">with pleasure</hi>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
                     If you fold it up carefully &amp; put it<lb/>
                     between the <del>covers</del>
               <hi rend="underline">pasteboard</hi> covers of<lb/>
                     a large octavo - or pasteboard cut to that<lb/>
                     size - &amp; <add>send it</add> in a cover directed to<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WardX1">R Ward Esq<hi rend="superscript">re</hi>
               </persName>
               <lb/>
                     Ordnance Office<lb/>
                     Pall Mall for <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
               <lb/>
                     with the enclosed note from me I think<lb/>
                     he will take care to frank it to me -<lb/>
                     and I hope that the shawl may be on<lb/>
                     my dear aunts shoulders by new<lb/>
                     years day -<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
                    You <hi rend="underline">see</hi> I am your very<lb/>
                    impatient &amp; pray believe<lb/>
                    me to be your very affect<lb/>
               <unclear/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
               <!--include linebreaks, if used. example: <closer> Yours<lb/> Very sincerely<lb/> -->
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p> The moment you tell me the price of<lb/>
                        the shawl I will send a draft or <lb/>
                  <unclear/>for the amount<lb/>
                  <!--A postscript goes here, outside the <closer>. -->
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <!--You can include a <pb/> here, or inside the postScript.-->
            <!-- Format for postscripts. 
               Postscripts do NOT go inside closer tags. Adjust to take into account the order in your letter. 
               Sometimes the signature is on page three, the address on page four, then the postscript follows back on the top of page one, for example.-->
            <closer><!--Use the <closer> element again to hold Address Leaf information.-->
               <address>
                  <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_unknown_03_page01.jpg"/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <lb/>
                  <placeName ref="./West-End-Hampstead_ENK">West End<lb/>
                            Hampstead</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <!--Include any text written on the address leaf; use a separate "addrLine" for each line and indicate line breaks. -->
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
               </address>
            </closer>
